						<summary>

						<p>Stone in a field near the village.</p>						

						<p>17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is very badly damaged. It seems to state that the wet field was a gift made by Hiriya-gauḍa of Hōmada-Hoṁnehaḷḷi under instructions from Basavaṁtapayya. The characters belong to 17th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
